## Goal

Automate infrastructure and deployments.

### Architecture improvement

```
GitHub
   ↓
CI/CD Pipeline
   ↓
Infrastructure Deployment
   ↓
Docker Containers
```

### Services / Tools

```
GitHub Actions
Terraform
Docker registry
AWS CLI
```

### Platform capability

* automated deployments
* infrastructure reproducibility
* consistent environment setup

---

# Phase 4 — Monitoring and Observability

## Goal

Gain visibility into platform health.

### Architecture addition

```
Containers
   ↓
Prometheus metrics
   ↓
Grafana dashboards
```

Logs pipeline:

```
Containers
   ↓
Loki
   ↓
Grafana logs
```

### Services / Tools

```
Prometheus
Grafana
Node Exporter
cAdvisor
Loki
Alertmanager
```

### Platform capability

* track CPU / memory
* detect outages
* receive alerts

---

# Phase 5 — Automated Client Provisioning

## Goal

Create WordPress sites automatically.

### Architecture addition

```
Admin Request
      ↓
Provisioning API
      ↓
Create Database
Deploy Container
Configure Nginx
Create DNS
Generate SSL
```

### Services / Tools

```
Node.js API
Docker CLI
AWS SDK
WP-CLI
Certbot
```

### Platform capability

* new client site created automatically
* provisioning time ~1–2 minutes
* minimal manual work

---

# Phase 6 — Performance Optimization

## Goal

Handle high traffic efficiently.

### Architecture addition

```
CloudFront CDN
      ↓
Nginx cache
      ↓
Redis object cache
      ↓
WordPress containers
```

### Services / Tools

```
CloudFront
Redis
Nginx caching
```

### Platform capability

* high traffic handling
* reduced database load
* faster page delivery

---

# Phase 7 — High Availability

## Goal

Ensure platform remains online during infrastructure failures.

### Architecture upgrade

```
Load Balancer
      ↓
Multiple EC2 nodes
      ↓
Container cluster
```

Database:

```
RDS Multi-AZ
```

### Services / Tools

```
AWS ALB
Auto Scaling Group
RDS Multi-AZ
```

### Platform capability

* no single server failure
* traffic distributed
* platform redundancy

